entry.summary: ...EXCESSIVE HEAT WARNING REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM AST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Heat indices at or greater than 112 degrees Fahrenheit. * WHERE...The urban and coastal sections from the west through the north to the San Juan Metropolitan Area, Culebra, Vieques and St Croix.

entry.summary: ...HEAT ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 PM AST THIS AFTERNOON... * WHAT...Heat indices of 108 to 111 degrees Fahrenheit. * WHERE...The urban and coastal sections from southwest to the east of Puerto Rico and St. Thomas, St. John and Adjacent Islands.

entry.title: Beach Hazards Statement issued September 25 at 4:06AM CDT until September 25 at 10:00PM CDT by NWS
entry.summary: ...BEACH HAZARDS STATEMENT IN EFFECT THROUGH THIS EVENING... * WHAT...Dangerous swimming conditions are expected along the Lake Superior shoreline due to high wave action and strong rip currents. * WHERE...Minnesota Park Point and Wisconsin Point Beaches. * WHEN...Through this evening.
